This paper deals with the optimization of bi-directional scheduling and linear precoding and equalization for a multi-link MIMO two-way system. This involves the management of interference across the system, which is a key concern in the field of information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper deals with network optimization, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also involves the design of linear transceivers, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). The use of MIMO technology and optimization of linear precoding and equalization also falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a simple algorithm for joint optimization, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques (cs.LG).
